OL,5, Labour's deputy leader Angela Rayner   
OL,6, has admitted she is relaxed about      
OL,7, people becoming "filthy rich... as long
OL,8, as they pay their taxes".              
OL,10,FShe said Labour wants people to "create
OL,11,Fwealth", echoing famous remarks made by
OL,12,Fthe party's former spin doctor, Peter  
OL,13,FMandelson.                             
OL,15,FSpeaking to the BBC's Political        
OL,16,FThinking podcast, Ms Rayner was asked  
OL,17,Fabout her views on wealth and class.   
OL,19,FAsked if Labour believed in aspiration,
OL,20,Fshe said: "Absolutely, 100%."          
